To the seventeenth century belongs the work of Vertranius, N. Heinsius, and Freinsheim. I. F. Gronovius died in 1671, before the publication of liis edition, which was completed by his son, Iao. Gronovius, also editor of the Variorum edition of 1721. In 1687 came Theodorus de Rycke. Ernesti's useful Variorum edition was published in 1752. The nineteenth cen- tury editors of the Annals include Waltlmr, Ruperti, Heraeus, Orelli, Baiter, Ritter, Halm, Nipperdey, Haase, Doderleim Drager. Furneaux died in the last year of the century.
